### Project API Examples
### Make sure to replace UUIDs with actual values from your database

### 1. Create a new project
POST http://localhost:4000/api/projects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "client_id": "12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012",
  "title": "E-commerce Website Development",
  "description": "Need a modern e-commerce website with payment integration",
  "category": "Web Development",
  "budget": 3500.00
}

###

### 2. Get all projects (no filters)
GET http://localhost:4000/api/projects

###

### 3. Get projects with filters
GET http://localhost:4000/api/projects?category=Web Development&budget_min=1000&budget_max=5000&status=pending&page=1&limit=5

###

### 4. Get specific project by ID
GET http://localhost:4000/api/projects/12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012

###

### 5. Update project details
PATCH http://localhost:4000/api/projects/12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated E-commerce Website Development",
  "budget": 4000.00,
  "description": "Need a modern e-commerce website with payment integration and admin panel"
}

###

### 6. Update project status
PATCH http://localhost:4000/api/projects/12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress"
}

###

### 7. Delete project (soft delete)
DELETE http://localhost:4000/api/projects/12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012

###

### Error Examples

### 8. Try to create project with missing fields
POST http://localhost:4000/api/projects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "client_id": "12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012",
  "title": "Incomplete Project"
}

###

### 9. Try to get project with invalid UUID
GET http://localhost:4000/api/projects/invalid-uuid

###

### 10. Try to update with invalid status transition
PATCH http://localhost:4000/api/projects/12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "completed"
}

###